by J. K
The results have been released for a Valentine’s Day survey!
Many Koreans celebrate Valentine’s Day as a holiday where females give males a gift of chocolate. On March 14, known as White Day, males respond by giving females gifts.
Seven Edu, an internet math education company for middle and high school students, conducted a survey from January 21 to February 11 to find out which star people would want to give chocolate to for Valentine’s Day. The survey included 10,670 respondents.
Kang Daniel came in first place with 51.4 percent (5,484) of the votes! BTS’s Jimin took second with 40.2 percent (4,285).
See the top five below:
1. Kang Daniel (51.4 percent)
2. Jimin (40.2 percent)
